descriptionMarkdown:
Basically, it links roboport logistic networks without linking the robots. Also creates a stockpile of items in your main base so that the separate logi-network doesn't drain your whole base.
It works by creating a separate logistics network to come off your main bases logistic network. It "reads all" so it will work with any and ALL mods. It keeps a stockpile of a certain amount of items in your base, so the alternative logi-network doesn't steal all your resources from main base - while you can still supply all necessary resources to the alternative logistic network. (Main base is the requester-chest side).

This is version 6. Version 5 works perfectly well, but i haven't done a full test of this version. The difference is, version 6 reads for inventory resources of values less than 10..... if you don't understand then don't worry haha

Originally, i wanted to "read" what the outpost logistic network was needing for construction that were "missing materials for construction", I was going to funnel this into requester chests in the main base and have them transfer items to passive providers in the outpost network, but there is no way to do that, so i came up with the idea to simply read all via a chest and supply anything over a certain limit (eg, anything over 200). 
Then with version 6 i realise i maybe i want to supply some items that you generally dont produce over 200 of (eg, nuclear reactors) so i added another little circuit network/requestor chest (the requestor above the other one) to fix that. If it screws up you can simply delete the top requestor and then you basically have version 5 of the blueprint. 
ENJOY!
title: Logistic Network Linker (LNL) - By Aero182218
